4 HR____ DECLARING FEBRUARY 24, 2026, AS ALABAMA LINKS DAY AT
5 THE CAPITOL.
6
7 WHEREAS, The Links, Incorporated, is an
8 international, nonprofit corporation established in 1946 and
9 is one of the nation's oldest and largest volunteer service
10 organizations committed to enriching, sustaining, and
11 ensuring the culture and economic survival of African
12 Americans and other people of African ancestry; and
13 WHEREAS, the Southern Area Links Days at the Capitol
14 were established by 16th Southern Area Director Margaret
15 Thompson Johnson to inspire Links members and chapters
16 across the Southern area to work toward ensuring that
17 legislation was in place to eliminate health disparities in
18 the Southern area states and the Commonwealth of the
19 Bahamas; and
20 WHEREAS, the Alabama chapters of The Links,
21 Incorporated, will celebrate 21 years of gathering at the
22 Capitol under the theme "Lead with Intentional Friendship
23 and Service" on February 24, 2026; and
24 WHEREAS, the national priorities of Civil Rights,
25 Women's Health Equity, Education, Equal Pay and Economic
26 Empowerment, Social Justice and Public Safety, and
27 Environmental Justice and Climate Change remain at the
28 forefront of issues that the Alabama chapters advocate for;
Page 1

forefront of issues that the Alabama chapters advocate for;
HR153 INTRODUCED
29 and
30 WHEREAS, in addition to national priorities, the
31 Alabama chapters focus on the needs of the Southern Area of
32 Links, Incorporated, including the ideals of transforming
33 communities through service, promoting civic engagement, and
34 collaborating for legislative impact; and
35 WHEREAS, the members of the Alabama chapters look
36 forward to a robust discussion and continued engagement with
37 lawmakers in the State of Alabama to ensure that policy and
38 laws are passed that have a positive impact and outcomes for
39 the communities the members belong to and serve; now
40 therefore,
41 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
42 LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, That February 24, 2026, is hereby
43 declared Alabama Links Day at the Capitol, and this
44 resolution serves to honor the organization's mission with
45 best wishes for collaborative impact and success.
